#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:236 3bdae07493c54ee2a8708545d779b340
msgid "Inverse problem: topology optimization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:238 767a49bb82ac4be98dcb8d2ec98227fa
msgid ""
"The inverse-problem benchmark exercises the **differentiability** of "
"TensorMesh on a classical topology-optimization task: compliance "
"minimization of a 2D cantilever beam using the Solid Isotropic Material "
"with Penalization (SIMP) method. We compare against JAX-FEM, the only "
"other framework in the list above that supports end-to-end automatic "
"differentiation through the FEM pipeline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:246 e89491437b9b4c0aa83d48cb6d3c6725
msgid "Problem setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:248 df5f659068894905ab01cf1e9458f25b
msgid ""
"The computational domain is a rectangle :math:`\\Omega = [0, L_x] \\times"
" [0, L_y]` with :math:`L_x = 60` and :math:`L_y = 30` (dimensionless), "
"discretized into :math:`60 \\times 30` bilinear quadrilateral (QUAD4) "
"elements — 1,891 nodes and 1,800 elements. Homogeneous Dirichlet "
"conditions are imposed on the left edge,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:254 1f729db04a154bd98ea1928ecdc3e321
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\mathbf{u} = \\mathbf{0} \\quad \\text{on } \\Gamma_D = \\{(x,y) : x = "
"0\\},"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:258 9edc332aa59747ceab2810e07f44b86c
msgid ""
"and a distributed traction is applied to the lower portion of the right "
"boundary,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:261 e31808c403794e2d87a26864358034cf
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\mathbf{t} = (0,\\, -100)^\\top \\;\\text{N/m}\n"
"\\quad \\text{on } \\Gamma_N = \\{(x,y) : x = L_x,\\; 0 \\leq y \\leq "
"0.1\\, L_y\\}."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:266 70b344348f8e4276b344160b3863653b
msgid "Cantilever boundary conditions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:271 897240d54b9146c3b87211eb17b36c6f
msgid "The element stiffness is parameterized by the SIMP interpolation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:273 226633d5991b414bbeebd3d8d2c98c5e
#, python-brace-format
msgid "E(\\rho) = E_{\\min} + \\rho^p \\,(E_{\\max} - E_{\\min}),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:277 a66fa5ec305743bfad131e8234875357
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"where :math:`\\rho \\in [\\rho_{\\min}, 1]` is the element-wise density "
"(the design variable), :math:`p = 3` penalizes intermediate densities, "
":math:`E_{\\max} = 70{,}000` MPa is the solid stiffness, and "
":math:`E_{\\min} = 70` MPa keeps the stiffness matrix non-singular. The "
"Poisson's ratio is :math:`\\nu = 0.3`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:283 708f6627b4904c5983eeb8a360583ad2
msgid ""
"The optimization minimizes structural compliance subject to a volume "
"constraint:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:286 2bd40c7381a64c2e81fd4cb2c88badde
msgid ""
"\\begin{aligned}\n"
"    \\min_{\\boldsymbol{\\rho}} \\quad\n"
"        & C(\\boldsymbol{\\rho})\n"
"          = \\mathbf{u}^\\top \\mathbf{K}(\\boldsymbol{\\rho}) "
"\\mathbf{u}\n"
"          = \\mathbf{F}^\\top \\mathbf{u} \\\\\n"
"    \\text{s.t.} \\quad\n"
"        & \\frac{1}{|\\Omega|} \\int_{\\Omega} \\rho \\, d\\Omega \\leq "
"\\bar{v} \\\\\n"
"        & \\mathbf{K}(\\boldsymbol{\\rho}) \\mathbf{u} = \\mathbf{F} \\\\"
"\n"
"        & \\rho_{\\min} \\leq \\rho_e \\leq 1, \\quad \\forall e\n"
"\\end{aligned}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:299 4969388c404f4d8bba5198dc81ad312b
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"with target volume fraction :math:`\\bar{v} = 0.5` and "
":math:`\\rho_{\\min} = 10^{-3}`. We use the Method of Moving Asymptotes "
"(MMA) with move limit :math:`\\Delta\\rho_{\\max} = 0.1` and a "
"sensitivity filter of radius :math:`r_{\\min} = 1.5\\,h` (where :math:`h`"
" is the element size) to suppress checkerboard patterns. The optimization"
" runs for 51 iterations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:307 27399fed60354be595595fbf1ef604a2
msgid "Sensitivity via automatic differentiation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:309 5567ee3f12574c43b58fd6f94f74a176
msgid "The classical adjoint-method sensitivity for SIMP has the closed form"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:311 3734cadf9cb8409ba758edc5e27dd2e1
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\frac{\\partial C}{\\partial \\rho_e}\n"
"= -p\\, \\rho_e^{p-1} (E_{\\max} - E_{\\min})\\,\n"
"  \\mathbf{u}_e^\\top \\mathbf{K}_0^e \\mathbf{u}_e,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:317 63ba935f04bc46f58667aba420e5812b
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"where :math:`\\mathbf{K}_0^e` is the element stiffness at unit Young's "
"modulus. In TensorMesh this gradient is **not implemented manually** — it"
" is obtained by backpropagating through the differentiable assembly and "
"sparse solve via PyTorch's reverse-mode autograd. The closed-form "
"expression above is reproduced only for reference and as a consistency "
"check against the autograd output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:325 5d31bc62fb3f4ada8f13a8d2814c8f5d
msgid "Final design comparison"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/performance/benchmarks.rst:327 a7920980f171453a90c448294a4fbc9c
